# Test failure diagnosis and fix

When **any** test fails (`mvn verify`, module `test`, or CI), follow this workflow before changing code. Do not guess; do not weaken production behaviour to green a test.

## 1. Collect evidence

Run the **smallest repro** first, then widen if needed:

```bash
# Single test (preferred)
mvn -pl <module> test -Dtest=ClassName#methodName -Dformatter.skip=true -Dspotless.skip=true

# Single test class
mvn -pl <module> test -Dtest=ClassName

# Full gate (after fix)
mvn verify
```

Gather artifacts:

| Source | What to read |
|--------|----------------|
| `*/target/surefire-reports/*.txt` | Stack trace, suppressed exceptions, timeout vs assertion |
| `*/target/surefire-reports/TEST-*.xml` | Per-method timing, parameterized index `[n]` |
| Test stdout/stderr | STOMP frames, transport connect URL, broker ports |
| CI log | Docker availability, port conflicts, parallel runs |

Re-run the **failing test alone**. If it passes alone but fails in the suite → suspect **test infra** (shared state, ports, parallel execution, container reuse).

## 2. Classify root cause

Write a one-paragraph analysis with a **single primary bucket**:

| Bucket | Signals | Fix location |
|--------|---------|--------------|
| **Test defect** | Wrong URL/port/path, wrong STOMP version rules, `pollDelay` > Awaitility timeout, `SEPARATE_THREAD` + shared broker, missing `settleSubscription`, assertion does not match spec | Test class or test resource only |
| **Test infra** | `StompContainer` / `broker.xml` mismatch, wrong mapped port (TCP **61613**, WebSocket **61614**, OpenWire **61616**), container reuse with stale image, `junit-platform.properties` parallel + fixed ports | `*.tests.infra`, `src/test/resources/broker.xml`, `junit-platform.properties` |
| **Production defect** | Fails alone and in suite; behaviour contradicts [STOMP spec](https://stomp.github.io/stomp-1.2.html) or [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md); regression introduced by recent change | `src/main` in correct module |
| **Environment** | Docker not running, OOM, CI timeout on slow broker startup | Document; do not change protocol code |

**Normative references** (read before changing behaviour):

- STOMP spec: [stomp.github.io](https://stomp.github.io/) — wire format, command order, headers, heart-beats, ack semantics
- Library vocabulary: [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md)
- Protocol rule: [stomp-protocol-compliance.mdc](stomp-protocol-compliance.mdc)

## 3. Decision rules (mandatory)

1. **Spec wins** — If production code matches the STOMP spec and the test does not, fix the **test**. If production code deviates from the spec, fix **production** and add tests that would fail if it regresses.
2. **No implementation breakage** — Do not remove receipts, ack handling, framing, or API contracts solely to pass a test. Do not add sleeps, `@Disabled`, or widen timeouts without fixing the underlying race or misconfiguration.
3. **Minimal diff** — One root cause per change set. Do not mix unrelated test stabilisation with feature work.
4. **Module placement** — Protocol/framing → `commons` tests; client behaviour → `client`; embedded server flows → `server` (avoids Maven cyclic test deps).
5. **Verify in the right module** — `commons` unit → `mvn -pl commons test`; broker-backed → `mvn -pl client test` or `server test` with Docker.

## 4. Stable test framework (OO and infra)

Reuse and extend existing abstractions; do not duplicate broker wiring per test.

| Type | Use | Do not |
|------|-----|--------|
| Broker integration | `StompContainer` + `StompActiveMqContainer` | Raw `stomp://localhost:61613` or ad-hoc Testcontainers |
| Embedded server | `StompServer.builder()` + unique port per test/method | Shared port across parameterized or parallel tests |
| Async waits | Awaitility with `atMost` > `pollDelay` | `Thread.sleep()` |
| Concurrency | `@Execution(SAME_THREAD)` + `junit.jupiter.execution.parallel.enabled=false` when sharing ports/broker | `SEPARATE_THREAD` + shared static container without isolation |
| WebSocket Artemis | `ws://host:<mapped 61614>` + `Sec-WebSocket-Protocol` subprotocols (`v12.stomp`, …) | `ws://…:61616` (OpenWire) or `/stomp` path unless broker requires it |
| TCP client transport | `MessageBuffer` incremental decode | Extra `\n` after encoded frames |

**Test infra OO boundaries:**

- `StompContainer` — JUnit extension; lifecycle and parameter resolution only
- `StompActiveMqContainer` — broker image, ports, credentials, URLs (`tcpUrl`, `webSocketUrl`)
- Test classes — scenario and assertions only; no embedded Docker logic

When adding infra, prefer **one class, one responsibility** and package-private helpers in `*.tests.infra` (e.g. frame builders shared by server protocol tests).

## 5. Fix checklist

Before marking done:

- [ ] Failing test re-run alone **and** in full module suite passes
- [ ] Root cause documented in commit/PR (test / infra / production)
- [ ] **Report file** written under `${mavenRoot}/reports/` after fix is green (see §6)
- [ ] No change contradicts STOMP spec or domain spec
- [ ] `mvn verify` passes once (Docker running) — not after every incremental fix
- [ ] If user-visible behaviour changed → [docs/features.md](../../docs/features.md); if gap closed → ARCHITECTURE.md §13
- [ ] Non-obvious fix rationale added as in-code comments per [stomp4j-in-code-documentation.mdc](stomp4j-in-code-documentation.mdc)

## 6. Failure report (mandatory after fix)

Write **one report file per root cause or fix session** — not one file per failed assertion while still iterating.

**When to write**

| Phase | Action |
|-------|--------|
| While investigating | Classify and fix; re-run single test or `mvn -pl <module> test` only |
| After module tests green | Create or update the report file |
| Trivial test typo / wrong port in test only | Optional report; still document in commit message |

Skip the full report template for obvious one-line test fixes (wrong import, typo in expected string). Always report **production defects** and **non-trivial infra** fixes.

**Location:** `${mavenRoot}/reports/`

`${mavenRoot}` is the directory that contains the root `pom.xml` (repository root in this project). Create the `reports/` folder if it does not exist.

**Filename:** `{sequential}-test-failure-{module}-{TestClass}-{methodName}-{yyyy-MM-dd-HHmmss}.md`

- **`{sequential}`** — zero-padded counter (`001`, `002`, …) so directory listing sorts reports in creation order. Before creating a file, list `${mavenRoot}/reports/` and set `{sequential}` to one more than the highest existing prefix on any `*-test-failure-*.md` file (or `001` when the folder is empty or missing).
- Omit `{methodName}` when the whole class failed or the root cause spans the class.
- Use `unknown` for the method name when not yet isolated.
- Example: `003-test-failure-client-StompClientTcpTest-shouldDeliverMessage-2026-06-29-143022.md`

### Report template

Copy this structure into every report:

```markdown
# Test failure report

## Failing test
- **Module:**
- **Class:**
- **Method:**
- **Command used to reproduce:**

## Why it failed
- **Classification:** test defect | test infra | production defect | environment
- **Exception / assertion:**
- **Evidence:** (surefire excerpt, log line, or frame dump)
- **Root cause:** (one paragraph)

## Fix
- **Files changed:**
- **What changed:**
- **Why this fix is correct:** (does not weaken receipts, acks, framing, or API contracts)

## STOMP spec alignment
- **Spec version:** 1.0 | 1.1 | 1.2
- **Relevant spec section(s):** (command, header, heart-beats, ack, … — link or cite [stomp.github.io](https://stomp.github.io/))
- **How the failure or fix relates to the spec:** (expected wire behaviour, command order, header semantics)
- **Domain spec:** (only if [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) adds library invariants beyond the normative spec)
```

Update the report after the fix is verified green. If classification or spec interpretation changes during investigation, amend the same file rather than creating duplicates.

## 7. User summary

When reporting to the user, include the same four areas as the report file:

1. **Failing test** (module, class, method)
2. **Why it failed** (classification + evidence)
3. **Fix** (what changed and why it does not break implementation)
4. **STOMP spec alignment** (version, section, relationship to expected behaviour)

Point to the report path: `${mavenRoot}/reports/<sequential>-test-failure-….md`.

